 1. Detail discussion of flexbox 
Flexbox is a one-dimensional layout system for aligning items horizontally or vertically in a container.
It uses properties like display: flex, justify-content, and align-items to control spacing, alignment, and order.
 2. Detail discussion of Grid
Grid is a two-dimensional layout system that lets you align items in rows and columns.

It uses display: grid, grid-template-columns/rows, and gap to create complex responsive layouts easily.

3-Basic use of Chrome dev tools
Use Inspect Element (Right-click > Inspect) to analyze and edit HTML/CSS live in  browser.

The Elements panel helps to view structure, while the Styles tab shows active CSS and allows testing layout changes.
